HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 407
BY REPRESENTATIVE WALTERS
A RESOLUTION
To express the condolences of the House of Representatives on the death of Spencer Leak,
Jr., vice president of Leak & Sons Funeral Home.
WHEREAS, it is with immense sadness and profound regret that the House of
Representatives of the Legislature of Louisiana has learned of the passing of Spencer Leak,
Jr.; and
WHEREAS, Spencer Leak, Jr., was the vice president of Leak & Sons Funeral
Homes; he helped lead the business for decades while upholding his family's legacy of
service; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Leak recently led and planned the funeral of Reverend Jesse
Jackson, Jr.; his family has deep ties to Chicago's civil rights movement, and his grandfather
led the march to desegregate Chicago's Oakwood Cemetery; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Leak was a tireless advocate for families who could not afford a
burial, a champion of Chicago businesses, and a generous mentor to entrepreneurs
throughout the city; and
WHEREAS, Spencer Leak, Jr., was a respected leader, devoted public servant, and
pillar of the Black community in Chicago; he will be deeply missed, but his legacy shall live
on in the hearts and minds of those who were privileged to have known and loved him.
THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the House of Representatives of the
Legislature of Louisiana does hereby express heartfelt condolences on the death of Spencer
Leak, Jr., and does hereby extend sincerest wishes that his family, friends, and loved ones
find comfort in their shared memories of his beautiful life.
